race.comment: FRANKIE'S ME DAD (6) didn't really inspire confidence last start, but a repeat of the start prior should be good enough to win a race of this nature. Beaten only a neck that day and finished in front of Tierra, who was an impressive winner at Kilmore earlier in the week. Should be at peak fitness now after three runs back from a spell and was probably going to drift back anyway, so the outside alley is not a complete disaster. TAVISTOCK DANCER (3) backs up after breaking a long drought last week and should press forward from the wide draw. They look the main three chances. Of the rest, TOGANMAIN (5) might be next best as a recent placegetter who has drawn well. A BLUE STAR (8) might be the roughie who can sneak a first four spot.
